    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to evaluate the sensitivity of pump-induced hemolysis to variations in component dimensions for a centrifugal blood pump used during cardiopulmonary bypass surgery. Model influence is MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect tolerance decision could impact clinical hemolysis levels). Model Risk Level 2.",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to identify worst-case operating conditions for hemolysis across 5 flow-speed combinations for a Class II CPB device. Results compared against predicate device hemolysis using relative hemolysis index (RH < 1 acceptance criterion).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "name": "COU1: Cardiopulmonary bypass use (Class II)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-cfd-hemolysis-worst-case",
      "type": "Claim",
      "name": "CFD model reliably identifies worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump",
      "description": "The CFD model of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump has been subjected to extensive verification and validation activities, including grid-independence studies across three mesh refinement levels, comparison of predicted velocity fields against particle image velocimetry data from the FDA benchmark dataset, and evaluation of hemolysis index predictions against in-vitro bench measurements at five flow-speed operating points. Across all evaluated conditions, the model demonstrated RH values below 1.0 relative to the predicate device, consistent with the acceptance criterion. The body of computational and experimental work supports the assertion that the CFD model is credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions within the defined context of use at Model Risk Level 2. This claim is grounded in the full 13-factor ASME V&V 40 credibility assessment documented in the associated credibility evidence package, and the convergence of independent validation streams gives high confidence that the model predictions are fit for the intended regulatory decision.",
      "purpose": "Establish model credibility for regulatory submission supporting worst-case hemolysis identification in CPB device tolerance analysis",
      "scope": "FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry; 5 flow-speed operating combinations; Class II CPB device; RH < 1 acceptance criterion relative to predicate device"
    }
  ],
